<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The shareholders of publicly traded hedge fund=
 management firm Sculptor Capital Management Inc. have a choice between two=
 options:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sculptor has signed a merger agreemen=
t to sell itself to Rithm Capital Corp. for $11.15 per share. It is asking =
shareholders to approve that deal. If they vote yes, then they will almost =
certainly get cashed out at $11.15 per share.<a class=3D"footnote-index" hr=
ef=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: in=
line-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Somebody else has offered to buy =
Sculptor for $12.76 per share. Sculptor=E2=80=99s board of directors says t=
hat this offer is too risky: Its financing is=C2=A0uncertain, and this offe=
r (like Rithm=E2=80=99s) is conditional on at least a majority of Sculptor=
=E2=80=99s hedge fund=C2=A0<em>clients=C2=A0</em>approving the new owner.=
=C2=A0Sculptor=E2=80=99s board says that the clients might not=C2=A0approve=
 the new owner, in which case the $12.76 deal would fall apart and sharehol=
ders would be left with nothing.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footno=
te-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !im=
portant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
